Deployment exists, but:

kubectl get pods
No resources found

👉 What could be wrong?
👉 What to check first?

Solution:-
Possible Causes:

• Replica count = 0
• Wrong namespace
• Selector mismatch
• Image issues
• Controller not working

Correct Debug Flow
1️⃣ Check Deployment
kubectl describe deployment <name>
2️⃣ Check ReplicaSet
kubectl get rs
3️⃣ Check Events
kubectl get events
4️⃣ Check Namespace
kubectl get pods -n <namespace>
5️⃣ THEN check Controller Manager

# Most Common Real Issue

 Namespace mismatch
Wrong labels/selectors
